* Finance Minister Christine Lagarde speaks to finance
commission 12:30 p.m.
* Question Time 3:00 p.m.
* Finance Minister Christine Lagarde speaks to the Senate
finance commission 4:15 p.m.
* Interior Minister Claude Gueant speaks on road safety at
Tremblay-en-France 4:30 p.m.
* President Sarkozy meets fishing industry representatives
at the Elysee Palace 6:00 p.m.  EQUITIES:
* Eutelsat Communications SA (ETL FP): The world’s third-
largest satellite company said it had third-quarter revenue
of 295.2 million euros, up 10 percent from year-earlier
levels. Eutelsat also raised its full-year revenue forecast
to more than 1.16 billion euros.
* Havas SA (HAV FP): The advertising company renewed
 Vincent Bollore ’s mandate as chairman, and said it will pay
its 2010 dividend on May 17.  MARKETS:
*The CAC 40 Index gained 1.1 percent to 4,052.51
*The broader SBF 120 Index rose 1.1 percent to 3,047.91  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
